Marinara Sauce

28oz can whole San Marzano tomatoes
1/4 c evoo
7 garlic cloves, peeled and slivered
small dried whole chile, or pinch of crushed red pepper flakes
1 tsp kosher salt
1 large fresh basil sprig, or 1/4 tsp dried oregano or more to taste

Pour tomatoes into a large bowl and crush with your hands. Pour 1 c water into can and slosh it around to get tomato juices. Reserve. In a large skillet over medium heat, heat the oil. When it is hot, add garlic. As soon as garlic is sizzling (do not let it brown) add tomatoes, then the reserved tomato water. Add whole chile or pepper flakes, oregano (if using) and salt. Stir. Place basil sprig, on the surface. Let it wilt, then submerge in sauce. Simmer until thickened and oil on surface is a deep orange, ~15min. If using oregano, taste sauce after 10 min, adding more salt and oregano if needed). Discard the basil and chile.
